<br>
When I hear a statement like that, makes me wonder if you really have been playing since Beta.  Verant has a notorius reputation for making the same mistakes...over...and over...and over again.  They made the mistake of unbalancing the game with added levels and equipment upgrades for half the classes in Kunark.  They made the mistake of putting too powerful weapons in the hands of the player in Velious, trivializing encounters quickly, followed by heavy handed nerfs (remember the Vulak rogue dagger anyone?), as well as class disciplines that were nowhere near balanced or well thought out.  They made the mistake of once again making the player too powerful with new weapons and AA advancement trivializing encounters.  I have friends on Rodcet who say they can do AoW in about 10 minutes now.  They like to brag, but they always back that up with fact.  Then there's manaburn wizzies, AM3 rangers, caster focus 3 being putting on twink items etc.  The list just goes on.<br>
<br>
Verant has such a poor track record of overpowering the player, followed by heavy handed nerfs.  Either that, or a poor understanding of RvR.  VP, NToV, ST, Ssra Temple, VT.  When Kunark came out, the &quot;ubber&quot; drops of back then was dropping of zone trash mobs.  Practically the entire Luclin expansion was not itemized, or over itemized.  I remember the early icewell keep raids in which not even pp dropped, only to hear about ubber Guilds raiding PoG (hard to believe ubber Guilds raided PoG at any point, but its true) had loot coming out of their ears!  Followed by the nerf after they were done farming.  Oh, and Sleepers...oh yeah, that was quality SoE entertainment there.  &quot;Rar!  I'm awake, and I've 2,000 year old blue ball!  Time for my one mob gangbang.  Skyshrine, here I come!&quot;<br>
<br>
Being in since beta means nothing if you've been playing with your eyes closed the entire time.  And saying if you don't like it, don't play is certainly the wrong way to look at it.  We pay money for a service.  If that service is not rendered to our satisfactory, we have every damn right to complain.<br>
<br>
This of course is not word, and not law, but my opinion.  Differ if you may, but I'm tired of paying to beta test this game.  I want something done right for once.  The first time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uevenightdarkfang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evenight Darkfang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 8:44:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WTF!? Level 65!?</span><hr size=1> Granted, I have also been playing since Beta. I've seen the same mistakes made over and over as has been stated, but I've decided to give SOE a second chance recently. After the disembarking of Brad and the death of the former "Vision", the development team really does have a game that they are trying to pull up. A lot of folks have to admit that some of the changes that happened recently, while cosmetic in origin, have been very nice and well received. The one issue that folks still seem to have is balance and exactly how to make everyone feel "useful". Its in that endeavour that SOE still seems to be failing. <br>
<br>
If they tell me that its not going to be a grind to level 65, I will believe them... but I'm curious to find out how. Someone has claimed that it is due to planar advancement. None of this is substantiated, but they claim that as you get to new locations in the planes, you can talk to NPCs which raise you to the next tier in PXP (planar XPs) and through this raise your literal level. All it takes is fighting your way up through the planes in order to get the new levels. As was said, that is one theory and there are a lot going around... Some fairly good and promising, and some are downright bad... <br>
<br>
We're just all going to have to wait and see how things turn out... If in the end, its a trainwreck, it makes no difference whether folks quit now or then... But if it works out, quitting now over hearsay will seem pretty silly. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uevenightdarkfang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evenight Darkfang</A> at: 9/23/02 8:44:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uragedemon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RageDemon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ragedemon.clanpages.com/jap.bmp" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 6:10:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ragedemon.clanpages.com/profile.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WTF!? Level 65!?</span><hr size=1> Well Kunark came out, you had 10 more levels (and longer level) to finish.<br>
